</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Thailand-Car Thief </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Jobless, cash-strapped Thai man turns car thief for food
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) _ A jobless man who drove a car through a
showroom window and hoped to sell it for food has been arrested for
theft, police said Monday.
	   Police said Yodrak Namthao, 23, broke into a used car showroom
in downtown Bangkok Sunday morning and crashed a Saab 9000 through
a front glass panel, but was stopped by police on his way out of
town.
	   The man told police that he was not a natural-born thief, but
needed money for food while he has been looking for a job. He said
he had been out of work for three months.
	   Police report that robbery and petty crimes have risen in the
wake of an economic crisis which has left more than one million
without jobs.
	   The Labor Office anticipates the number of unemployed may reach
two million by the end of this year. 	   
</TEXT>
