<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-New Zealand-Asian Killed </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Detectives turn attention to missing Japanese tourist
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   AUCKLAND, New Zealand (AP) _ Police investigating the death of
an unknown Asian woman said Monday that they were now seeking
information on a Japanese tourist missing for 2 1/2 weeks.
	   Kayo Matsuzawa, 29, had not been seen since she checked into a
backpackers' hostel in downtown Auckland, Det. Senior Sgt. Kevin
Baker said.
	   He said dental records were being sought from Japan to establish
whether she was the woman found dead in a stairwell electrical room
in a central Auckland building last week.
	   Matsuzawa arrived in New Zealand at the end of last year and
police understand she originally stayed with another Japanese woman
in Christchurch.
	   On Sept. 11, she traveled by herself to Auckland to spend two
weeks sightseeing before a planned return to Christchurch.
	   Baker said she checked into the hostel that afternoon, paying a
deposit on her room, where she put her belongings before going out.
	   pjs
</TEXT>
