<SLUG> BC-Ukraine-Nuclear </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Reactors stopped, restarted at Ukraine's nuclear power plants
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KIEV, Ukraine (AP) _ A reactor was stopped at Ukraine's
Zaporizhia nuclear power plant in advance of repairs that are
scheduled to last several months, officials said Monday.
	   Reactor No. 3 was shut down early Sunday and is scheduled to be
restarted Dec. 10, the state nuclear energy company Energoatom
said.
	   Another reactor at Zaporizhia, Europe's largest nuclear plant,
was restarted Saturday after three days of repairs. The plant has
six Soviet-designed VVER-1000 reactors.
	   A total of 14 malfunctions have occurred at Zaporizhia in the
first seven months of this year, more than at any other Ukrainian
nuclear energy facilities, according to the plant's data.
	   A minor malfunction was also reported Sunday in the safety
system of a reactor at the Rivne nuclear power plant. As a result,
the reactor was shut down and restarted within an hour.
	   Ukraine has five nuclear power plants, which account for more
than 40 percent of the former Soviet republic's electricity
production.
	   (vl/ji) 	   
