<HEADLINE>
Russian Economy Minister leaves for G-7 meeting
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Russian Economy Minister Andrei Shapovalyants left
Monday for meetings in London with his counterparts from the Group
of Seven industrialized countries, the ITAR-Tass news agency
reported.
	   The ministers will be discussing problems related to Russia's
financial crisis.
	   President Boris Yeltsin named Shapovalyants to the post on
Friday.
