<SLUG> BC-Israel-Shooting, 1st Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Shots fired at Israeli students in Hebron, one injured
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES throughout with details on shooting, CORRECTS that
injured was a female student, not seminary student &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   HEBRON, West Bank (AP) _ Shots were fired Monday at a group of
Israeli students in downtown Hebron, and one girl was lightly
injured, Jewish settlers and Israeli radio reports said.
	   Settler spokesman Noam Arnon said the students were headed
toward the Jewish enclave of Tel Romeida when shots were fired at
them from the Palestinian-controlled part of town.
	   Israel radio said one female student was shot in the leg.
	   Tensions between Jewish settlers and Palestinians in Hebron rose
considerably last month after a settler rabbi was stabbed to death
in his home in Tel Romeida, a cluster of several trailers in the
heart of a Palestinian neighborhood. The assailant, presumably a
Palestinian militant, was never caught.
	   In response, settlers overturned stalls in outdoor markets and
beat up Palestinian passers-by on several occasions.
	   Hebron is home to 130,000 Palestinians and 450 Jewish settlers.
In January 1997, Israeli troops handed 80 percent of the city to
Palestinian control, but remained in the downtown area to protect
the settler enclaves.
