<HEADLINE>
Dollar up, gold down
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ The U.S. dollar rose against other major
currencies in early European trading Monday. Gold fell.
	   Dollar rates compared with late Friday:
	   _1.6818 German marks, up from 1.6668
	   _135.94 Japanese yen, up from 134.38
	   _1.3864 Swiss francs, up from 1.3742
	   _5.6400 French francs, up from 5.5897
	   _1.8963 Dutch guilders, up from 1.8806
	   _1,662.81 Italian lire, up from 1,648.63
	   _ 1.5111Canadian dollars, down from 1.5113
	   The British pound was quoted at dlrs 1.6950, down from dlrs
1.7032.
	   London dealers fixed a recommended gold price of dlrs 293.80 bid
per troy ounce at midmorning, down from the closing price of dlrs
296.30 Friday.
	   In Zurich gold traded at dlrs 293.25, down from dlrs 299.50.
	   Gold rose 20 cents in Hong Kong to dlrs 293.95.
	   Silver opened in London at dlrs 5.17 bid per troy ounce, down
from dlrs 5.20.
