<HEADLINE>
Canadian embassy invaded by Albanian refugees
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: LEADS to UPDATE with new figure and information &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   BUDAPEST, Hungary (AP) _ Thirty-four Albanian refugees have
forced their way into the Canadian embassy Monday demanding asylum,
the Hungarian state-run radio reported.
	   There are 18 adults and 16 children in the group, Hungarian
police spokesman Mihaly Dezsi told state radio.
	   If the negotiations fail, Hungarian refugee authorities have
indicated readiness to house the Albanians.
	   Embassy officials, engaged in negotiations with the refugees,
were not available for comment.
	   Hungarian police have sealed off the area around the embassy,
which is a fenced-in compound of two larger buildings in the hills
of Buda, a quiet residential part of the city.
