<HEADLINE>
MUNICH: said Monday.
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   Waigel, who has headed the party for 10 years and is Kohl's
finance minister, told a CSU leadership meeting that he will not
run for re-election as party chairman at a convention in January,
said the sources, speaking on condition of anonymity.
	   Bavarian governor Edmund Stoiber, who led the party to a strong
victory in state elections two weeks ago, is considered Waigel's
likely successor.
	   Many thought that the CSU victory would give a boost to Kohl in
Sunday's national election, but instead the conservative camp also
recorded heavy losses in Bavaria, a traditional stronghold.
	   Kohl announced Sunday night he would not run again as party
chairman.
