<SLUG> BC-Hong Kong-Drug Arrest </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Customs officers detain Mexican woman after seizure of cocaine
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   HONG KONG (AP) -Customs officers have detained a Mexican woman
following the seizure of 9.2 kilograms (20.2 pounds) of cocaine
from an unclaimed suitcase at Hong Kong airport, officials said
Monday.
	   They said the cocaine, which would have fetched 11 million Hong
Kong dollars (U.S. dlrs 1.4 million), was found Saturday hidden in
boxes labeled as coffee in the suitcase that arrived on a flight
from Japan.
	   The Mexican, whose name was not disclosed, was detained
following a raid on a hotel on Sunday, they said.
	   She was believed to have arrived in Hong Kong from Brazil via
Tokyo, customs officials said.
	   The 33-year-old suspect has been charged with drug-trafficking.
