<HEADLINE>
FA lodges misconduct charge against player for shoving ref
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: Updates with FA charge lodged &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ Italian striker Paolo Di Canio of Sheffield
Wednesday was charged with misconduct Monday by the Football
Association for shoving a referee to the ground _ an act which
could result in a lengthy ban from the English game.
	   The FA gave Di Canio 14 days to respond to the charge and
request a personal hearing over what was described as a ``reported
assault'' on referee Paul Alcock.
	   Di Canio pushed Alcock after being sent off during Saturday's
1-0 win against Arsenal at Hillsborough.
	   Danny Wilson, Sheffield Wednesday's manager, announced an
immediate suspension of Di Canio pending sanctions from the FA.
	   The FA's misconduct charge could result in a six-month ban or
even in an expulsion from the Premier League.
