<HEADLINE>
BONN, Germany: conservative rule
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   The Social Democratic victory marked the first time in postwar
Germany that voters rejected all parties from the previous
government in favor of fresh faces and new ideas.
	   The Greens, which won 6.7 percent, get their first shot at
entering government if the talks are successful. Schroeder said his
party would try to assemble a coalition as quickly as possible. But
negotiations could be difficult between two parties with widely
differing policies.
	   Schroeder offered assurances that Germany's foreign policy would
remain constant, addressing anxieties about how the pacifist wing
of the Greens might affect Germany's role in NATO and in
international security.
