<HEADLINE>
St. Petersburg official killed in explosion
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; RETRANSMITTING to fix garble &QL; 
 &UR; Eds: CORRECTS spelling of last name to ``Agaryov.''

<TEXT>
	   ST. PETERSBURG, Russia (AP) _ A high-ranking official
responsible for providing municipal services in St. Petersburg was
killed early Monday in a bombing.
	   Yevgeny Agaryov, the deputy chairman of the northern city's
committee on consumers, was killed when he opened the door of his
sixth-floor apartment, Russian news agencies reported. Police
believe he was killed by a radio-controlled bomb in a contract
murder.
	   Dozens of St. Petersburg businessmen and government officials
have been killed in recent years, many of them in apparent disputes
over state property. The killings are blamed on organized crime and
are rarely solved.
