<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Oceania Cup </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Australia beats Cook Islands 16-0
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BRISBANE, Australia (AP) _ Australia stayed on course to reach
the Confederations Cup soccer tournament with a 16-0 win over the
Cook Islands in the Oceania Cup competition Monday.
	   Australia and New Zealand were top of their respective
three-team pools in the six nation qualifying tournament for next
year's finals in Mexico.
	   New Zealand added an 8-1 win over Vanuatu to its 1-0 win over
Tahiti on Friday while Australia won its first match 3-1 over Fiji,
also Friday.
	   Australia took an 8-0 halftime lead Monday with Damian Mori
scoring four times before being replaced at the break. Robert
Trajkovski scored four after halftime and Paul Trimboli got a
hat-trick.
	   New Zealand's Vaughan Coveney scored four goals before being
replaced at halftime in its comfortable victory.
 &UR; (tjh)
</TEXT>
