r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Sports-RugbyL-Austral     09-28 0096
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-RugbyL-Australia-Drugs </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Player banned for steroids
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SYDNEY, Australia (AP) _ Australian first grade rugby league
player Ben MacDougall has been suspended for 22 matches after
pleading guilty to a steroid charge.
	   MacDougall's brother Adam is one of four other top level players
who received suspensions for returning positive tests this year.
	   Ben MacDougall, a center with Western Suburbs, tested positive
on April 8 and waived his right to a hearing by pleading guilty,
the Australian Rugby League announced Monday.
