<HEADLINE>
Brtish coach suspended on child pornography charges
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ A leading British amateur swimming coach was
suspended Monday following his arrest on child pornography charges.
	   The action against Steve Davis, head coach at Northampton
Swimming Club, was announced by the Amateur Swimming Association
and the British Swimming Coaches and Teachers Association.
	   The BSCTA said Davis was arrested last Friday ``for allegations
of involvement in child pornography on the Internet.''
	   Police said Davis was charged with possession of indecent
photographs of children with intent to distribute or show. He was
released on bail and ordered to appear in court on Oct. 30.
	   The association said the allegations do not relate to any
involvement with Northampton swimmers.
	   ``However, it wishes to make it clear that it does not condone,
nor support, such behavior or practices. ...
	   ``While Mr. Davis has been a successful coach, and is a highly
respected member of the British coaching fraternity, his admittance
of the allegations leave the BSCTA will no alternative but to take
the action that it has.''
