<SLUG> BC-Sports-Baseball-Japan Roundup </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Swallows beat BayStars 11-2
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TOKYO (AP) _ Dwayne Hosey smashed a three-run home run in the
seventh as the Yakult Swallows trounced the Central League's
front-running Yokohama BayStars 11-2 at Tokyo's Jingu Stadium
Monday.
	   Hosey, formerly with the Boston Red Sox, has 13 homers.
	   The BayStars are still five games ahead of the second-place
Chunichi Dragons who were idle Monday.
	   No other Central Leauge games were scheduled Monday.
	   In the Pacific League, Norio Tanabe singled home the winning run
in the bottom of the ninth, giving the front-running Seibu Lions a
4-3 victory over the Kintetsu Buffaloes at Seibu Dome.
	   The Lions have a 1 1/2 game lead over the second place Nippon
Ham Fighters who lost to the Chiba Lotte Marines 3-1 at Chiba.
	   Kenji Yoshitsuru of the Marines singled home two runs in the
fifth inning and drove in another run in the seventh with a
sacrifice fly.
	   Satoru Komiyama scattered six hits over eight innings for his
11th victory against 11 defeats.
	   No other games were scheduled Tuesday.
 &UR; (sk) 	   
