<SLUG> BC-Turkmenistan-Railways </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Turkmenistan to electrify rails with EU backing
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ The European Union is sponsoring a dlrs 300
million project to electrify Turkmenistan's railways, a news agency
reported Monday.
	   The four-year program is intended to electrify 335 kilometers
(208 miles) of railways in the former Soviet republic in Central
Asia, saving it a little more than dlrs 3 million a year, Interfax
said.
	   According to the report, the project is run by the European
Union's program for technical assistance to members of the
Commonwealth of Independent States, the loose coalition of former
Soviet republics.
	   (ml)
</TEXT>
