<SLUG> BC-Dollar-Gold, 1st Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Dollar mostly higher, gold down
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; EDS: UPDATES with late rates &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ The U.S. dollar was higher against most other
major currencies in late European trading Monday. Gold prices fell.
	   Dollar rates compared with late Friday:
	   _1.6774 German marks, up from 1.6668
	   _135.62 Japanese yen, up from 134.38
	   _1.3890 Swiss francs, up from 1.3742
	   _5.6248 French francs, up from 5.5897
	   _1.8914 Dutch guilders, up from 1.8806
	   _1,658.71 Italian lire, up from 1,648.63
	   _1.5109 Canadian dollars, down from 1.5113
	   The British pound was quoted at dlrs 1.7038, up from dlrs
1.7032.
	   Gold closed in London at dlrs 292.50 bid per troy ounce, down
from the closing price of dlrs 296.30 bid Friday.
	   In Zurich gold traded at dlrs 292.20, down from dlrs 299.50.
	   Gold rose dlrs 0.20 in Hong Kong to dlrs 293.95.
	   Silver closed in London at dlrs 5.17 bid per troy ounce, down
from dlrs 5.20 bid Friday.
	   (acw)
</TEXT>
