Aziz meets with Annan, U.N. inspection stalemate looms
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; URGENT &QL; 
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES with Aziz saying Iraq won't make concession &QL; 
 &UR; By NICOLE WINFIELD &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   UNITED NATIONS (AP) _ Iraqi Deputy Prime Minister Tariq Aziz
said Monday that Baghdad won't make concessions to end the standoff
over arms inspections, saying Iraq had complied fully with U.N.
resolutions demanding that it destroy its banned weapons.
