<TEXT>
	   ROME (AP) _ Italy's Davis Cup players will split 1.2 billion
lire (dlrs 700,000) as a reward for advancing to the final by
defeating the United States, Italian tennis federation president
Francesco Ricci Bitti said Monday.
	   Italy, which last won the Davis Cup in 1976, routed the United
States 4-1 this weekend, with Andrea Gaudenzi, Davide Sanguinetti
and Gianluca Pozzi registering singles victories and Gaudenzi
teaming with Diego Nargiso to take the doubles match.
