<HEADLINE>
Teenager kills cousin and burns his body
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KUWAIT (AP) _ Police arrested a 16-year-old Kuwaiti for brutally
killing his younger cousin over a ``strong personal dispute,'' the
Interior Ministry said Monday.
	   The burned body of a 13-year-old boy was found last week on the
roof of a building in al-Mangaf, south of Kuwait City.
	   The 16-year-old, who was not identified, told police that he had
asked his cousin to meet him on the roof of a residential building
so they could steal bicycles, a ministry statement said.
	   When his cousin showed up on the roof, he repeatedly stabbed
him, and when he fell to the ground, he slit his throat and burned
the body using kerosene.
	   The ministry statement did not elaborate on the dispute, or
provide any names.
