<HEADLINE>
Egypt pardons 2,300 prisoners for October War celebrations
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   CAIRO, Egypt (AP) _ President Hosni Mubarak has pardoned 2,300
prisoners to mark the 25th anniversary of the 1973 Arab-Israeli
war, police officials said Monday.
	   The amnesty does not cover prisoners convicted for terrorism and
vice, said the officials, speaking on customary condition of
anonymity.
