surprise and crossed the Suez Canal, which Israel had held since
capturing Egypt's Sinai peninsula in the 1967 Arab-Israeli war.
	   The Egyptians were later pushed back, but Arabs feel the initial
victory erased the shame of the 1967 defeat and allowed Egypt to
move toward peace.
	   It became the first Arab state to make peace with Israel in a
1979 treaty.
