<SLUG> BC-Cape Verde-Plane Crash, 1st Ld,0159 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Cape Verde prime minister injured in crash landing, one dead
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: LEADS with three grafs to CLARIFY in overline and lead that
plane made a crash landing STED crashed. &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   LISBON, Portugal (AP) _ The prime minister of the Cape Verde
islands was injured when the plane he was in made a crash landing
during a storm Monday, killing one of his bodyguards, according to
news reports.
	   Prime Minister Carlos Veiga was under observation at Agostinho
Neto Hospital in Praia, the capital of the island group 480
kilometers (300 miles) off the coast of Senegal, the Portuguese
news agency Lusa reported. He suffered bruises, but his injuries
were not life threatening.
	   One of Veiga's bodyguards died in the crash, Lusa quoted a
government source as saying. The other 18 people on board the plane
suffered slight injuries, the report said, but no details were
available.
