u i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Hungary-Canada-Refuge 1stLd-Writethru   09-28 0337
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Hungary-Canada-Refugees, 1st Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Police remove Kosovo Albanians occupying Canadian Embassy grounds
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES with police action &QL; 
 &UR; By ALEX BANDY &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   BUDAPEST, Hungary (AP) _ Hungarian riot police cleared the
grounds of the Canadian Embassy Monday after 34 ethnic Albanian
refugees invaded the compound and demanded political asylum.
	   No one was injured but some of the men had to be strong-armed in
the brief scuffle after about 100 riot police entered the compound
at 7 p.m. (1700 GMT) and hustled the refugees to a waiting bus.
	   Police waited for hours, hoping to persuade the 10 men and 8
women who had 16 children with them to leave quietly.
	   Canadian diplomats asked police to negotiate a settlement and
authorized a forcible eviction if the talks failed.
	   Police said the group occupying the embassy's front steps in a
slight rain had been identified as ethnic Albanians from
Yugoslavia's war-torn Kosovo province.
	   ``The group entered the embassy grounds a few minutes after 10
a.m. (0800 GMT) and demanded to be granted political asylum,''
police spokesman Mihaly Dezsi said.
	   He said the Albanians had been housed at a refugee camp in
Bicske, some 40 kilometers (25 miles) west of Budapest, since they
entered Hungary illegally.
	   They 34 people were returned to Bicske Monday evening.
	   ``Some members of the group had applied to emigrate to Canada,
but grew impatient and wanted to bring pressure on the Canadian
authorities,'' Dezsi said, explaining the motive behind the
occupation.
	   ``We will die here if we have to,'' one refugee yelled from the
embassy steps in the afternoon.
	   Offers of food were refused, and their spokesman explained they
brought plenty of supplies.
	   Embassy officials were not available for comment.
	   Hungarian police had sealed off the area around the embassy,
which is a fenced-in compound of two larger buildings in the hills
of Buda, a quiet residential part of the city.
	   (ab/rp) 	   
</TEXT>
