GERMANY: WRAP 2 - Gerhard Schroeder, Germany's future chancellor,
has begun talks with the Green Party as he seeks to forge the
coalition that will make up the country's next government.  APTN's
comprehensive election coverage continues with comments form
Schroeder, the Greens, Kohl, and general vox pops about the election
results. (F-L-A-S-H 1425/1030 F-L-A-S-H/1130 Europe Update/0900 The
Americas)
---
GERMANY: FIRST LADY - APTN profiles Doris Schroeder-Kopf - a
35-year-old former journalist, a mother of one, and wife of the
country's new Chancellor-elect. (Europe Update 1130)
---
KOHL: EUROPE 2 - APTN takes a look at how Germany has changed over
the last 16 years under Helmut Kohl and how Europe is slowly moving
towards the center left, as confirmed by the weekend election
result.  The piece includes reaction from British Prime Minister
Tony Blair, French Prime Minister Lionel Jospin, Russian communist
leader, Gennady Zyuganov, and a Europe analyst. (Europe Late 1500)
----
RUSSIA: GERMANY 2 - The change of leadership in Germany has been met
with fresh hopes in Russia for a prosperous financial partnership
between Bonn and Moscow. APTN brings you stock market reaction.
Meanwhile, Prime Minister Primakov is struggling to establish his
new cabinet, following the unexpected resignation of Deputy Prime
Minister Alexander Shokhin and the sacking of veteran reformer Boris
Fyodorov. (Europe Late 1500)
----
HEBRON: SHOOTING - Shots fired from the Palestinian sector of Hebron
wounded an Israeli woman, and Jewish settlers responded by beating
Palestinian passersby and overturning tables in an outdoor Arab
market. APTN the pictures. (F-L-A-S-H 1335)
----
US: HURRICANE - Latest pictures from the Gulf Coast where the the
population is bracing itself for the arrival of Hurricane Georges.
We also have aftermath pictures of Mississippi which was badly hit.
Includes soundbites with emergency services personnel. (Europe Late
1500) PART NO ACCESS US/CBC/AUSTRALIA
----
SERBIA: KOSOVO - Serb Prime Minister Mirko Marijanovic claimed
victory in parliament on Monday against ethnic Albanian separatists
in Kosovo. Our piece also includes the UN high commissioner for
refugees, Sadaka Ogata, visiting refugees in Kosovo. (Europe Late
1500) PART NO ACCESS YUGOSLAVIA
----
FRANCE: LE PEN - Jean-Marie Le Pen, France's far-right National
Front leader, has begun his appeal of a two-year political ban
for physically attacking a Socialist politician. (Europe Update
1130)
----
US: MIDEAST - APTN has the arrival of  Israeli Prime Minister
Benjamin Netanyahu and Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat in
Washington ahead of their meeting with US President Bill Clinton.
(Europe Late 1500)
-----
MALAYSIA: VIOLENCE - APTN brings you violent scenes form Kuala
Lumpur where anti-government demonstrators clashed with riot police
whom were seen kicking and hitting protestors with batons as they
tried to make their way through the capital. (Europe Late 1500)
----
RUSSIA: CHESS - One of Russia's poorest republics, Kalmykia, is
pushing for fame and more investment in its bid to host the upcoming
chess Olympics. Millions in public funds have been spent on building
the lavish but controversial Chess City. (Europe Update 1130)
PART NO ACCESS UK/FOX/CNN/CNBC/EURONEWS /AUSTRALIA
