<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Italy-People-Mutter </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Renowned solo violinist to play Beethoven concert in Milan
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ROME (AP) _ Devoting a one-year, round-the-world tour to the
works of just one composer doesn't get boring, renowned solo
violinist Anne-Sophie Mutter said Monday _ if that composer is
Beethoven.
	   The German-born musician takes her Beethoven's sonatas tour to
Milan's Teatro alla Scala on Oct. 8.
	   ``Beethoven's sonatas are so diverse and stretch over such a
long period; it gives you a panoramic view,'' Mutter said Monday at
a news conference on her tour.
	   Compared to standard tours featuring a few works by several
composers, ``This has emancipated the violin,'' she said.
	   The concert in Milan will feature three sonatas spanning 15
years, reflecting Mutter's intentions of showing the changes in
Beethoven's methods and moods over his life.
	   Mutter is performing with pianist Lambert Orkis.
	   (src)
</TEXT>
