<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Brazil-Abortion,0361 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Court of appeals authorizes 10-year-old rape victim to have
</HEADLINE>
abortion &QL; 
 &UR; By STAN LEHMAN
 &UR; Associated Press Writer

<TEXT>
	   SAO PAULO, Brazil (AP) _ The court of appeals in a Brazilian
state on Monday upheld the right of a pregnant 10-year-old rape
victim to have an abortion.
	   The girl _ who is 4-months pregnant _ was repeatedly raped over
the past three years by two neighbors in Israelandia, a small rural
town about 900 kilometers (560 miles) northwest of Sao Paulo in the
central state of Goias.
	   Judge Goncalo Teixeira e Silva said by phone that he turned down
an appeal to prevent the abortion ``because the law clearly states
that such procedures can take place in cases of rape or if
childbirth threatens the mother's life.''
	   A local judge, Joao Geraldo Machado, said the two men have been
arrested and face jail sentences of up to 10 years.
	   The two men ``offered food, candy and crackers to the girl to
lure her into a house where they raped her,'' Machado said, citing
the testimony of an 11-year-old girl forced to guard the house.
	   State attorney Reuder Cavalvante Motta had contested Machado's
initial authorization of the abortion Sept.16.
	   ``I am normally opposed to abortion,'' Machado said last week.
``But in this case I am in favor of it. The law allows it and I
think the girl's welfare depends on it.''
	   Motta disagreed, saying ``the constitution guarantees the right
to life, including intrauterine life. And I don't think the girl's
health or welfare will be affected if she gives birth.''
	   Appellate Court Judge Teixeira e Silva said the abortion has not
been scheduled and that doctors would first have to determine if
the girl's life would be imperiled by the procedure.
	   Meanwhile, local church officials have offered food, clothing
and other support to persuade the girl and her parents to keep the
child.
	   The girl's father, Manoel Batista de Souza was quoted by a local
newspaper as saying he favored the abortion ``because I fear for my
daughter's life.''
	   ``I fear the wrath of God, but we'll go through with the
abortion if the court says we can, '' he said last week.
</TEXT>
