<SLUG> BC-Sports-Track-Vebjorn Rodal,0210 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Rodal fires coach
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   OSLO, Norway (AP) _ After ten years close cooperation, 800-meter
runner Vebjorn Rodal fired his coach Kjell Arve Husby on Monday.
	   ``We have received information that is very hard to relate to.
Because of personal reasons, I cannot say what this information is
about,'' Rodal told Norwegian news agency NTB.
	   Husby has followed Rodal to many successes on the field: second
in the European Athletics Championship in 1994, third in the World
Championship in 1995 and gold in the Atlanta Olympics in 1996.
	   ``We have had no problems in our relationship, but the new
information has made it problematic. This is a tough day, but
hopefully also the end of a difficult time,'' said Rodal who
informed Husby personally Monday.
	   Still, Rodal still considers Husby a friend.
	   ``What we said is between me and him. He has been a creative and
skilled coach to me, also on the interpersonal level,'' Rodal said,
but he would not comment on a possible new cooperation between them
in the future.
	   Husby himself did not comment, but his lawyer, Morten Kjensli,
said that Husby was disappointed that Rodal did not wait a couple
of days to get the complete picture.
</TEXT>
