<SLUG> BC-Venezuela-Stock Market,0117 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Caracas stock market jumps by 7.2 percent
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   CARACAS, Venezuela (AP) _ The Caracas stock market jumped by 7.2
percent Monday, the biggest gain among major Latin American stock
markets.
	   Stock brokers said the the market was rallying because of the
stability of the currency, the bolivar, which entered its third
week of strengthening, and by a recovery in slumping oil prices.
	   Since Sept. 15, the bolivar has gained 2.2 percent against the
U.S. dollar. It closed Monday at 576 bolivars per U.S. dollar.
	   The stock market has jumped by 25 percent since Sept. 21. It had
fallen sharply since June when prices for Venezuelan oil hit a
12-year low.
</TEXT>
