<HEADLINE>
New, old faces on Brazilian soccer team
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) _ Flavio Conceicao and Elber are
back. Ronaldo isn't, yet.
	   There were a few surprises on the Brazilian soccer team
announced Monday by Coach Wanderley Luxemburgo for an exhibition
game with Ecuador Oct. 14 in Washington, D.C.
	   Striker Elber of Bayern Munich and midfielder Flavio Conceicao
of Spain's Deportivo La Coruna will return to the team after an
absence of many months.
	   Defenders Anderson of Santos and Cesar of Portugesa were named
for the first time, part of Luxemburgo's campaign to renew and
rejuvenate the team.
	   Ronaldo was not called. The two-time player of the year
reportedly has knee pains and has not played for his club, Inter of
Milan.
	   Most of the 22 players were on Luxemburgo's first team, which
tied 1-1 with Yugoslavia this month.
	   Player and clubs:
	   Goalies: Andre (Internacional) and Rogerio (Sao Paulo)
	   Defenders: Cafu (Roma), Felipe (Vasco), Serginho (Sao Paulo),
Cris (Corinthians), Antonio Carlos (Roma), Cesar (Portuguesa),
Odvan (Vasco), Anderson (Santos)
	   Midfielders: Alex (Palmeiras), Rogerio (Palmeiras), Vampeta
(Corinthians), Marcos Assumpcao (Flamengo), Jackson (Sport), Flavio
Conceicao (Deportivo La Coruna), Marcelinho (Corinthians) and
Rivaldo (Barcelona)
	   Forwards: Elber (Bayern Munich), Fabio Junior (Cruzeiro),
Christian (Internacional), Denilson (Betis),
</TEXT>
