<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-AP News Digest,1147 </SLUG>


<TEXT>
	   WORLD AT 0000 GMT:
	    &UR; NEW:
	   _GERMANY-HOW KOHL LOST. Unemployment was key issue.
	   _JAPAN-RECESSION'S CASUALTIES. Hokkaido residents hit hard.
	   _ALBANIA. Socialist Premier Fatos Nano resigns after rioting.
	    &UR; MAIN SPOT NEWS:
	   WASHINGTON _ President Bill Clinton sets a mid-October goal for
concluding a West Bank accord based on a report from Israeli Prime
Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat
that they had basically resolved how much land Israel will yield.
US-MIDEAST. RECAP expected by 0300 GMT. By Barry Schweid. AP Photos
WX103-104, 107, AWH201,202,205.
	   Also:
	   UNITED NATIONS _ Yasser Arafat asks world leaders Monday to
support Palestinian statehood but refrains from a unilateral threat
to declare a state next May. UN-PALESTINIANS. RECAP expected by
0300 GMT. By Nicole Winfield. AP Photos UNI113,115,117,118.
	   Has moved:
	   _ISRAEL-LAND PROTESTS. Protests by Israeli Arabs widen in scope.
	   _ISRAEL-PALESTINIANS. Tensions high in Hebron after Israeli
woman shot. AP Photos JRL101-105.
	   BONN, Germany _ The nation's future chancellor, Gerhard
Schroeder, made one thing clear after winning power as the voice of
change: Change will happen, but not too much for the good of
Germans, who cherish predictability. GERMANY-ELECTIONS. Expected by
0300 GMT. By Tony Czuczka. AP Photos
BON110,120,125,127,128,130,133,134; FRA107, HBG102.
	   Also:
	   _GERMANY-HOW KOHL LOST. Failure to tackle unemployment cost Kohl
his job. Expected by 0300 GMT.
	   _EUROPEAN LEFT. Schroeder's victory in Germany continues
leftward swing. Expected by 0300 GMT.
	   _GERMANY-ELECTION-INDUSTRY. German industry wary of left's
election victory. Has moved.
	   _US-GERMANY-SCHROEDER. Clinton expects close ties with future
German chancellor. Has moved.
	   WASHINGTON _ Federal Reserve policy-makers are expected to cut
interest rates for the first time in nearly three years on Tuesday,
acting on Chairman Alan Greenspan's alarm about a deteriorating
world economy. US-FINANCIAL CRISIS. RECAP expected by 0300 GMT. By
Martin Crutsinger.
