<SLUG> BC-Weather Summary,1072 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands from
the National Weather Service.
	   The combination of a low-level trough to the south of Puerto
Rico and the Virgin Islands, an upper-level trough directly over
Puerto Rico and a cold front north of Puerto Rico is creating
unsettled weather conditions across the region.
	   This will become more evident later on tonight and Tuesday, as
the low-level trough and the upper-level trough drift northward
overnight and Tuesday.
	   The wind will become more northeasterly on Tuesday and then
easterly or southeasterly on Wednesday, but will remain light
around 10 miles an hour or less.
	   The swells in the Atlantic waters from the northeast will
gradually subside through Wednesday.
	   San Juan and the northern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers.
Slight chance of a coastal thunderstorm. Low 75 to 80. Wind
variable less than 5 mph.
	   Tuesday... Partly cloudy with a 50 percent chance of showers.
Slight chance of a thunderstorm. High 85 to 90. Wind northeast at
10 mph.
	   Tuesday night... Partly cloudy. A 40 percent chance of showers.
Slight chance of a coastal thunderstorm. Low 75 to 80.
	   Wednesday... Mostly sunny in the morning. Partly cloudy in the
afternoon with a 20 percent chance of showers. High around 90.
	   Eastern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers.
Slight chance of a thunderstorm. Low 75 to 80. Wind variable less
than 10 mph.
	   Tuesday... Partly cloudy with a 40 percent chance of showers.
Slight chance of a thunderstorm. High 85 to 90. Wind east to
northeast 10 mph.
	   Tuesday night... Partly cloudy. A 40 percent chance of showers.
Low 70 to 75.
	   Wednesday... Mostly sunny. A 20 percent chance of showers. High
85 to 90.
	   Ponce and the southern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy. A 20 percent chance of showers. Low 70
to near 80. Wind light and variable.
	   Tuesday... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers.
Slight chance of an afternoon thunderstorm mostly inland. High 90
to 95. Wind southeast 10 to 15 mph.
	   Tuesday night... Partly cloudy evening with a slight chance of
showers then becoming generally fair. Low 70 to 75. Chance of rain
is less than 20 percent.
	   Wednesday... Mostly sunny. A slight chance of showers mainly
afternoon. High 90 to 95. Chance of rain is less than 20 percent.
	   Mayaguez and the western sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy. A slight chance of showers or an
evening thunderstorm. Low 70 to 75. Wind variable less than 10 mph.
Chance of rain is less than 20 percent.
	   Tuesday... Mostly sunny in the morning. Variable cloudiness in
the afternoon with a 50 percent chance of showers and
thunderstorms. High 85 to 90. Wind northeast 10 to 15 mph, except a
variable wind less than 10 mph along the west coast in the
afternoon.
	   Tuesday night... Generally fair. Low 65 to 75.
	   Wednesday... Sunny morning. Partly cloudy afternoon with a 30
percent chance of showers. Possibly a late afternoon thunderstorm.
High 85 to 90.
	   Interior sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy. A 20 percent chance of showers or an
evening thunderstorm. Low 65 to 70 mountains to 70 to 85 low
valleys. Wind light and variable.
	   Tuesday... Partly cloudy in the morning. Variable cloudiness in
the afternoon. A 50 percent chance of showers and thunderstorms...
Mainly afternoon. High from near 75 mountains to 85 to 90 lower
elevations. Wind northeast 10 mph.
	   Tuesday night... Becoming generally fair except partly cloudy
east with a 30 percent chance of showers until midnight. Low 65 to
70 mountains to 70 to 75 in lower valleys.
	   Wednesday... Sunny morning. Partly cloudy afternoon with a 30
percent chance of showers. Possible thunderstorm. High from 75 to
80 mountains to 85 to 95 low elevations.
	   St. Thomas, St. John and the Adjacent Islands-St. Croix:
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy. A 20 percent chance of showers. Slight
chance of a thunderstorm. Low 75 to 80. Wind variable less than 10
mph.
	   Tuesday... Partly cloudy with a 50 percent chance showers.
Slight chance of a thunderstorm. High around 90. Wind northeast 10
mph.
	   Tuesday night... Partly cloudy. A 30 percent chance of showers.
Low 75 to 80.
	   Wednesday... Mostly sunny. A 20 percent chance of showers. High
around 90.
	   Atlantic waters north and northeast of Puerto Rico and the U.S.
Virgin Islands:
	   Tonight... Wind north to northeast 10 kt or less. Seas 4 to 6 ft
in northeast swells. Widely scattered showers. Isolated
thunderstorms.
	   Tuesday... Wind northeast around 10 kt. Seas 3 to 4 ft in
northeast swells. Scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tue night... Wind east 10 kt or less. Seas 3 to 4 ft in
northeast swells. Scattered showers. Widely scattered
thunderstorms.
	   Caribbean waters south and southeast of Puerto Rico and the U.S.
Virgin Islands:
	   Tonight... Wind northeast to east 10 kt or less. Seas 2 to 4 ft,
except seas 4 to 6 ft in northeast swells in Atlantic passages.
Isolated showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tuesday... Wind east to southeast around 10 kt. Seas 2 to 4 ft,
except Atlantic passages seas 3 to 5 ft in northeast swells. Widely
scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tue night... Wind southeast 10 kt or less. Seas 3 to 4 ft.
Scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Near shore waters of western Puerto Rico:
	   Tonight... Wind northeast to north less than 10 kt. Seas 2 ft or
less. Isolated showers.
	   Tuesday... Wind east to northeast around 10 kt, except variable
10 kt or less along the coast. Seas 2 ft. Widely scattered showers.
Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tuesday night... Wind east to southeast less than 10 kt. Seas 2
ft or less. Scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Outlook for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands waters:
	   Wednesday through Friday... Wind becoming east and remaining 15
kt or less. Small to moderate northeast swells will prevail across
the local Atlantic waters through Wednesday.
</TEXT>
