<HEADLINE>
China congratulates Germany's Schroeder
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BEIJING (AP) _ China has congratulated Gerhard Schroeder and his
Social Democrats on winning Germany's election and expressed
confidence he would maintain warm bilateral ties.
	   Foreign Ministry spokesman Tang Guoqiang paid tribute to Helmut
Kohl, chancellor for 16 years before being unseated by Schroeder on
Sunday, and his work in improving Chinese-German relations.
	   ``The Chinese government and people will never forget Chancellor
Kohl's efforts in promoting these relations,'' the official Xinhua
News Agency paraphrased Tang as saying Monday.
	   ``We congratulate the German Social Democratic Party on winning
the national election. China has always valued its relations with
Germany,'' Tang was quoted as saying.
	   He also said China believed that as chancellor Schroeder will
continue to shepherd ties with Beijing. 	   
